          <physDesc>
            <p>Paper, about 6 3/4 in. by 4 7/8, consisting of 186 leaves, many
                                    of which are much torn, especially foll. 1—20, 38, 68—72, 78,
                                    83, 157, 158, 165—171, and 181—186. The quires, signed with
                                    letters, were probably 18 in number; but the volume is imperfect
                                    at the end, and there are lacunae after foll. 3, 9, 15, 171,
                                    178, 180, and 181. The number of lines in each page is 16 or 17.
                                 </p>
